<br>
In the books, as opposed to the movie, there is never any indication that Saruman is in fact a more powerful wizard than Gandalf. He did not assume the position as head of the order himself, but was rather elected to be the leader - it is mentioned that some of the other notable good characters in the books voted for Gandalf as leader, but were in minority. As for robes... Saruman's robes are a bit special in the books. They appear to be white, but after revealing his true position to Gandalf, they turn out to have all the colours of the rainbow. White was merely an illusion <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
