<br>
On subject, i believe Gandalf had something like a near death experience after his battle with the Balrog. He certainly only barely survived it. And that balrog was definitely something he feared, it was an even more powerful creature in the book than in the movie (movie balrog is just a huge fiery guy with a flaming whip - book balrog is that as well as a spellcaster of near gandalf's ability). So he had a very close encounter with death, and defeated something he feared greatly - that would certainly make a new person out of him. <p>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>
